<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05187</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE INTERNET GAMBLING REGULATORY ACT OF 2017</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to regulate online gaming by creating a regulatory Board which shall promulgate and adopt rules and regulations to govern Internet gaming; Also requires for an independent testing and certification standards for internet games and internet gaming devices and associated equipment; Provides for internet gaming account credits and payment and prohibits minors (under 18 yrs. old)from engaging in online gambling.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-03-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Bravo (M.) (097 2017-05-31)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GAMES AND AMUSEMENTS ON 2017-03-07</td></tr></table>